        "created_at": "2025-10-28T00:09:15.985Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I‚Äôve been doing a lot of advocacy for Signal. Recently someone pointed me to Threema‚Äôs criticism of Signal, which levels two criticisms I find hard to address:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://threema.com/en/blog/chat-apps-government-ties-and-transparency\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Chat Apps, Government Ties, and Transparency ‚Äì Threema</a>  links to Signal Foundation‚Äôs 2018 tax return and labels this ‚ÄúBrian Acton Injected over $100m into Signal‚Äù. I‚Äôm only aware of a $50m ‚Äúloan‚Äù mentioned in <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/signal-foundation/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal &gt;&gt; Blog &gt;&gt; Signal Foundation</a>. Is there a writeup anywhere that can clarify just how much folks like Acton currently fund (and therefore presumably control) the Signal Foundation?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The same article points to <a href=\"https://signal.org/bigbrother/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal &gt;&gt; Government Communication</a> as obviously unmaintained, as how can it be that Signal was compelled to disclose data to a government only once in the last 4 years? It feels highly improbable.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If anyone can point me to writeups/explanations/counterpoints, that‚Äôd be amazing.</p>",
