        "created_at": "2025-10-28T17:27:33.455Z",
        "cooked": "<p>also, the latest subpoena on the big brother page makes it clear governments finally understood what data they can get from Signal - sign up date, last connect. what benefit is that for a government, really?<br>\npreviously they asked for all sorts of things, none of which they got. but if now they know they get nothing, which is again evident in the latest subpoena, why would they keep subpoenaing? what do they have to gain from such a court battle?</p>",
